        "subtitle": "A powerful fictional dataset of superhero stats across Marvel and DC",
        "description": "This dataset features 200 fictional superhero and villain characters drawn from Marvel and DC universes. Each entry includes stats such as strength, speed, intelligence, combat skill, and overall power. It\u2019s a clean, beginner-friendly dataset with some intentionally missing values to simulate real-world data issues.\n\nGreat for:\n\nClassification (e.g., predicting alignment)\n\nRegression (e.g., predicting power score)\n\nClustering (e.g., grouping heroes by attributes)\n\nEDA & Visualization practice\n\n=== About this file ===\n\nAbout this file\nThe dataset consists of 1 CSV file:\nsuperhero_abilities_dataset.csv\nIt includes 200 rows \u00d7 10 columns, representing stats and attributes for fictional superheroes and villains. The data is randomly generated and suitable for model training, analysis, or visualization.\nNote: This dataset is initially for beginners so the size of data is minimal, I will update it based on feedback or feature extensions.\n\n\n=== Columns & descriptions ===\n\nName: Unique name of the superhero/villain (fictional characters)\nUniverse: Unique name of the superhero/villain (fictional characters)\nAlignment: Moral alignment: Hero, Villain, or Anti-Hero\nStrength: Physical power level (1 to 10; may have missing values)\nSpeed: Movement/combat speed (1 to 10; may have missing values)\nIntelligence: Strategic thinking and intellect (1 to 10; may have missing values)\nCombat Skill: Fighting proficiency and martial skill (1 to 10)\nWeapon: Primary weapon or power type (e.g., Tech, Magic, Sword)\nPower Score: Overall calculated power rating (40\u2013100)\nPopularity Score: Fictional public popularity rating (1\u2013100)\n",
